      "agentResultText": "All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**PropelAuth email/password authentication** has been added to the app:\n\n### New files\n- **`src/app/api/auth/[slug]/route.ts`** — PropelAuth route handler for login/logout callbacks\n- **`src/middleware.ts`** — Auth middleware that processes auth cookies on all routes\n- **`src/lib/auth.ts`** — `getAuthUser()` helper that validates the session and maps the PropelAuth user to a local Prisma user (creates one on first login via upsert)\n- **`src/components/user-nav.tsx`** — Client component showing Login/Sign Up buttons or the user's email + Logout button\n\n### Modified files\n- **`prisma/schema.prisma`** — Added `propelAuthId String? @unique` to the `User` model\n- **`src/app/layout.tsx`** — Wrapped app in `AuthProvider`, added `UserNav` to the navbar\n- **`src/app/dashboard/page.tsx`** — Requires auth via `getAuthUser()`, scopes posts to the logged-in user\n- **`src/app/dashboard/actions.ts`** — All actions (create/update/delete) authenticate and scope to the logged-in user's `id`\n- **`src/app/settings/page.tsx`** — Requires auth, loads the logged-in user's profile\n- **`src/app/settings/actions.ts`** — `updateUser` scopes to the authenticated user\n\n### How it works\n1. Unauthenticated users see **Login/Sign Up** buttons in the nav\n2. Clicking either redirects to PropelAuth's hosted auth page (email/password)\n3. After login, PropelAuth redirects back to `/api/auth/callback` which sets session cookies\n4. Protected pages (`/dashboard`, `/settings`) call `getUserOrRedirect()` — if no session, the user is redirected to login\n5. On first login, a local Prisma `User` record is created and linked via `propelAuthId`",
