      "agentResultText": "Build passes. The approach now:\n\n1. **Custom `/api/logout` route** — A GET handler that invalidates the refresh token via PropelAuth's backend API, then clears all three auth cookies (`__pa_at`, `__pa_rt`, `__pa_org_id`) using `NextResponse.cookies.set(\"\", { maxAge: 0 })` (which avoids the `Secure` flag issue), and returns a 302 redirect to `/login`\n2. **Full page navigation** — `window.location.href = \"/api/logout\"` ensures the redirect response's `Set-Cookie` headers are reliably processed by the browser (unlike `fetch` which can have edge cases)\n3. **Middleware exclusion** — `/api/logout` is excluded from the auth middleware so it won't try to refresh tokens before the route runs",
